  "market_context": "Strong bullish trend in the U.S. Dollar Index with consecutive higher highs and higher lows; analyst identifies multiple pullbacks within the uptrend on the 6-hour chart.",
  "key_observation": "In steep uptrends, pullbacks typically reverse near the 0.382–0.5 Fibonacci zone, not below 0.5; a bullish engulfing pattern confirmed reversal at that zone.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst configured a custom Fibonacci retracement tool by unchecking 0.236 and all levels above 0.5, keeping only 0, 0.382, 0.5, and 1, and matching 0.382 color to 0 and 1.",
    "Step 2: Anchored the Fibonacci from swing low wick (103.386) to swing high wick (104.462) on the DXY 6H chart.",
    "Step 3: Observed price pullback to the 0.382–0.5 zone (specifically near 103.797), where a bullish engulfing candle formed, signaling reversal.",
    "Step 4: Re-anchored Fibonacci from the next swing low wick to the subsequent swing high wick, confirming another pullback into the same 0.382–0.5 zone with strong bullish candle and continuation upward."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In strong trends, custom Fibonacci settings focusing on 0.382 and 0.5 help identify high-probability reversal zones; bullish engulfing patterns at these levels offer reliable continuation entries.",
